textAfterTable: Cerwin Vega V-Max VMX-10SVC  competition series sub woofer.  It is a single 4 ohm voice coil sub with 200w rms 600w MAX Power.  The VMX-10SVC is built with machined frame of aluminum, brass, and stainless steel. This sub is brand new, never been used or installed. They originally retailed for $160. 10" VMAX-10SVC Single Voice Coil Subwoofer Vega Maximum Throw Suspension Rugged Die Cast Aluminum Frame Built-in Passive Crossover Powerful Double Stack Magnet Assembly Titanium/Nickel Alloy Plated Diaphragm High Temperature Voice Coil Designed for Sealed or Vega Ported Enclosures The VMX-10SVC may also be used in single-tuned bandpass or vented enclosures if different results are desired, or if the application demands it. Using the VMX-10SVC in a vented enclosure will typically give you higher SPL capability than in a sealed enclosure, but with the penalty of additional group delay and compromised transient response.
